Hanjuku Hero
{{Short description|Video game series}}
{{nihongo|'''''Hanjuku Hero'''''|半熟英雄|Hanjuku Hīrō|"Soft-Boiled Hero"}}{{refn|group=Note|The [[kanji]] would normally be read ''eiyū'', but [[furigana]] (not displayed) indicate the intended reading.}} is a [[Japan]]-exclusive series of [[real-time strategy]] [[video game]]s. It is directed by [[Takashi Tokita]] and published by [[Square Enix]] (formerly [[Square (video game company)|Square]]). The series contains four main titles and a spin-off game. The main titles are ''Hanjuku Hero'' (1988), ''Hanjuku Hero: Aa, Sekaiyo Hanjukunare...!'' (1992), ''Hanjuku Hero Tai 3D'' (2003), and ''Hanjuku Hero 4: 7-Nin no Hanjuku Hero'' (2005). The spin-off is a Nintendo DS game called ''Egg Monster Hero'' (2005), which is a role-playing game with an emphasis on touch-based gameplay. The series is known for its humor and is centered on Lord Almamoon, the protagonist who must save his country from danger in each game.<ref name="HH4">{{cite web |last=Niizumi |first=Hirohiko |title=New details on next Square Enix Egg Monster games |url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/new-details-on-next-square-enix-egg-monster-games/1100-6108860/ |publisher=[[GameSpot]] |access-date=2016-01-29 |date=2004-09-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180214142144/https://www.gamespot.com/articles/new-details-on-next-square-enix-egg-monster-games/1100-6108860/ |archive-date=2018-02-14 |url-status=live}}</ref>

