{{nihongo|''Hanjuku Hero''|半熟英雄|Hanjuku Hīrō|"Soft-Boiled Hero"}} is the first game in the series, released in 1988 for Famicom. It was re-released on the [[Virtual Console]] in [[2007 in video gaming|2007]] for the [[Wii]], in 2013 for the [[Nintendo 3DS]] and in April 2014 for the [[Wii U]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nintendoeverything.com/super-punch-out-hanjuku-hero-hitting-the-japanese-wii-u-virtual-console-next-week/ |title=Super Punch-Out!!, Hanjuku Hero hitting the Japanese Wii U Virtual Console next week |publisher=Nintendo Everything |author=NE_Brian |date=2014-04-01 |access-date=2016-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205150758/http://nintendoeverything.com/super-punch-out-hanjuku-hero-hitting-the-japanese-wii-u-virtual-console-next-week/ |archive-date=2016-02-05 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Although the game did not receive a stand-alone soundtrack album release, a bonus disc of 17 tracks from the game was included in the soundtrack album to ''Hanjuku Hero VS 3D'', featuring some of the earliest work by [[Nobuo Uematsu]] of later ''[[Final Fantasy]]'' fame.<ref name="HH3dsoundtrack"/>

